# Comprehensive Tuple Tests for DatarScript
Show "=== Tuple Tests Start ===".

# Basic tuple creation
Set t1 to a tuple of 1, 2, 3.
Show "Basic tuple: " plus t1.

# Empty tuple
Set empty_tuple to a tuple of.
Show "Empty tuple: " plus empty_tuple.

# Nested tuples
Set nested_tuple to a tuple of 1, a tuple of 2, 3, 4.
Show "Nested tuple: " plus nested_tuple.

# Tuple concatenation (same type)
Set t2 to a tuple of 4, 5, 6.
Set concat_tuple to t1 plus t2.
Show "Concatenated tuple: " plus concat_tuple.

# Tuple indexing
Set first_item to item at 1 in t1.
Show "First item (1-based): " plus first_item.

Set second_tuple to item at 2 in nested_tuple.
Show "Second item of nested (tuple): " plus second_tuple.

# Tuple with variables
Set x to 10.
Set y to 20.
Set tuple_vars to a tuple of x, y, "hello".
Show "Tuple with variables: " plus tuple_vars.

# Tuple with different types
Set mixed_tuple to a tuple of 1, "string", true, false, 3.14.
Show "Mixed types tuple: " plus mixed_tuple.

# Tuple equality comparison
Set t3 to a tuple of 1, 2, 3.
Set equal_result to t1 is equal to t3.
Set unequal_result to t1 is equal to t2.
Show "t1 equals t3: " plus equal_result.
Show "t1 equals t2: " plus unequal_result.

# Tuple with arithmetic
Set arith_val to 5 plus 3.
Set arith_tuple to a tuple of arith_val, arith_val times 2, arith_val divided by 2.
Show "Arithmetic tuple: " plus arith_tuple.

# Test tuple length (can be inferred from equality with list length?)
# Tuples work with for-each loops
Set sum_items to 0.
For each item in t1, do:
    Set sum_items to sum_items plus item.
End for.
Show "Sum of tuple items: " plus sum_items.

# Logical operations on tuples
Set bool_tuple to a tuple of true, false, true.
Set logical_and to item at 1 in bool_tuple and item at 3 in bool_tuple.
Show "Boolean logic on tuple elements: " plus logical_and.




Show "=== Testing Immutability (should see errors) ===".


# Show "Testing Add to tuple:".
# Add 4 to t1.


# Show "Testing Subtract from tuple:".
# Subtract 1 from t1.


# Show "Testing Multiply tuple by 2:".
# Multiply t1 by 2.


# Show "Testing Divide tuple by 2:".
# Divide t1 by 2.


# Show "Testing Remove from tuple:".
# Remove last item from t1.

# Test tuple with conditionals
Set nonempty_tuple to a tuple of 42.
If nonempty_tuple is not equal to a tuple of, then:
    Show "Non-empty tuple has elements".
Else:
    Show "Should not happen".
End if.

# Empty tuple in conditional
If empty_tuple equals empty_tuple, then:
    Show "Empty tuple equals itself".
End if.

# Test tuple in arithmetic expressions
Set tuple_length to item at 1 in t1 plus item at 2 in t1 plus item at 3 in t1.
Show "Item 1 + 2 + 3 = " plus tuple_length.

Show "=== Tuple Tests Complete ===".